      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.pgrsaMY9kWHjVy4I]{Suspension}</p>\n<p>You can spend 2 Entropy Points as a reaction to trigger a chain reaction when you deal damage with your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.6Fuz5JTbJCBPynZd]{Entropic Strike (Su)} to an object or unliving creature, as long as that entropic strike was made as part of a standard action. Choose another object or unliving creature within 30 feet of the first target and make a second attack with your entropic strike at a –4 penalty. If you hit and can perform additional reactions that turn, you can use another reaction to perform a third attack against a different object or unliving creature.</p>\n<p>You determine line of sight and the range of this attack starting from one corner of the first target’s space. The second and third attacks are treated as attacks in a full attack for the purposes of abilities that reduce the penalties for full attacks.</p>"
